The paper discusses recommendation systems and topic modeling in the context of computer science conferences. The use of Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) for topic modeling suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions social networks and library websites, indicating a possible connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information science (cs.SI). Finally, the use of probabilistic topic modeling and semantic mining suggests a connection to deep learning (cs.DL).
